pting the reality with illusions. Weed out \n  the illusions.&quot; Once someo=\r\nne actually starts to weed out all obvious \n  illusions, eventually one rea=\r\nlizes that everything other than \n  unconditioned Self is an illusion anywa=\r\ny.\n\n  * * *\n\n  So I took the approach of accepting that the world is a real=\r\nity and then \n  rejecting things that can be deduced to be illusions.\n\n  Fo=\r\nr example, let me assume that &quot;I, Narasimha Rao, an individual being \n  in =\r\nthis world&quot; is not an illusion and a valid and true entity. I can \n  first =\r\naccept it to be real and then start analyzing various extensions \n  of that=\r\n entity. For example, people&#39;s views on this entity are formed \n  based on =\r\nan impression/reflection of this entity in their minds, which \n  is influen=\r\nced by this entity to some extent, but not fully. Just as my \n  reflection =\r\nin different mirrors may look different based on the colors, \n  dust, refra=\r\nctive properties etc of the mirrors etc, my reflection in \n  different mind=\r\ns may be different. Just as I cannot think that my \n  reflections in all mi=\r\nrrors around me are extensions of myself and start \n  celebrating or ruing =\r\nanything happeneing to those reflections, so should \n  I not think that my =\r\nreflections in the minds of people around me are \n  extensions of myself an=\r\nd start celebrating or ruing anything happening \n  to those reflections!\n\n =\r\n Thus, I can reject a lot of notions that I may tend to hang on to, as an \n=\r\n  illusion. This is what I am saying above. I may not be an illusion, a \n  =\r\nmirror (mind of someone) may not be an illusion, my image in the mirror \n  =\r\n(that person&#39;s notion of who I am) may not be an illusion, BUT my \n  thinki=\r\nng that my image in the mirror is an extension of my personality \n  is an i=\r\nllusion.\n\n  Similarly, we build complicated structures in our own minds reg=\r\narding \n  various external objects our senses perceive. When senses perceiv=\r\ne those \n  objects, mind thinks of a notional being that is far more compli=\r\ncated \n  than the objective reality represented by it! It is influenced by =\r\nmany \n  notions arising in our conditioning and not just based on the concr=\r\nete \n  objective reality. Again, such notions can be identified and rejecte=\r\nd as \n  illusions.\n\n  As you identify and reject each layer of obvious illu=\r\nsion about your \n  sense of who you are, who/what you are dealing with, you=\r\n eventually \n  realize unconditioned Self. Until then, &quot;jaganmithya&quot; is a m=\r\neaningless \n  and also perhaps a dangerous notion.\n\n  Best regards,\n  Naras=\r\nimha\n  ----------------------------------------------------------\n  Free Jy=\r\notish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n  &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; =\r\nritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\n  http://www.VedicAstrolo=\r\nger.org\n  Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org\n  Spiritu=\r\nality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n  Jyotish writings: http:=\r\n//groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n  Twitter ID: @homam108\n  --------=\r\n--------------------------------------------------\n\n  &gt; Dear Narasimha,\n  &gt;=\r\n\n  &gt;&gt; Jagat isnt mithya. Brahman is satya & jagat 2 is satya.\n  &gt;&gt; Neither =\r\nmirror nor ur image in it r &quot;illusions&quot;. They r &quot;real&quot;. But \n  &gt;&gt; ur thinki=\r\nng 1/2\n  &gt;&gt; that ur image in mirror is ur extension is an illusion.\n  &gt;&gt; Ex=\r\ncitement/sadness abt things happenin 2 d mirror image is an \n  &gt;&gt; illusion.=\r\n2/2\n  &gt;\n  &gt;\n  &gt; Can you please clarify the concept of satya & non-mithya in=\r\n light of\n  &gt; Vasishtha&#39;s words in Yoga Vasishtha (2.3.11 - 2.3.18)?\n  &gt;\n  =\r\n&gt; There is a chain starting from some examples which are obviously\n  &gt; mith=\r\nya (=E0=A4=A8=E0=A5=8C=E0=A4=B8=E0=A5=8D=E