s in the minds of =\r\npeople around me are \n  &lt;BR&gt;extensions of myself and start celebrating or r=\r\nuing anything happening \n  &lt;BR&gt;to those reflections!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Thus, I can rej=\r\nect a lot of notions that I \n  may tend to hang on to, as an &lt;BR&gt;illusion. =\r\nThis is what I am saying above. I \n  may not be an illusion, a &lt;BR&gt;mirror (=\r\nmind of someone) may not be an illusion, \n  my image in the mirror &lt;BR&gt;(tha=\r\nt person&#39;s notion of who I am) may not be an \n  illusion, BUT my &lt;BR&gt;thinki=\r\nng that my image in the mirror is an extension of \n  my personality &lt;BR&gt;is =\r\nan illusion.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Similarly, we build complicated \n  structures in our ow=\r\nn minds regarding &lt;BR&gt;various external objects our senses \n  perceive. When=\r\n senses perceive those &lt;BR&gt;objects, mind thinks of a notional \n  being that=\r\n is far more complicated &lt;BR&gt;than the objective reality represented \n  by i=\r\nt! It is influenced by many &lt;BR&gt;notions arising in our conditioning and \n  =\r\nnot just based on the concrete &lt;BR&gt;objective reality. Again, such notions c=\r\nan \n  be identified and rejected as &lt;BR&gt;illusions.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;As you identify a=\r\nnd reject \n  each layer of obvious illusion about your &lt;BR&gt;sense of who you=\r\n are, who/what \n  you are dealing with, you eventually &lt;BR&gt;realize uncondit=\r\nioned Self. Until \n  then, &quot;jaganmithya&quot; is a meaningless &lt;BR&gt;and also perh=\r\naps a dangerous \n  notion.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best \n  regards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;--------=\r\n--------------------------------------------------&lt;BR&gt;Free \n  Jyotish Softw=\r\nare, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; \n  ritual =\r\nmanuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A \n  href=3D&quot;http://www.Vedi=\r\ncAstrologer.org&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;B